What Are Dental Probes and Mirrors?
Dental probes are slender, calibrated instruments used to explore periodontal pockets, measure probing depth and detect sub‑gingival calculus. Dental mirrors provide a reflective surface that enhances visibility of posterior teeth and hard‑to‑see areas within the oral cavity. Together, they form the backbone of routine dental examinations, enabling clinicians to make accurate diagnoses and treatment decisions.
